premise_source_doc_sentence: Bronte Woodard  (  October 8 , 1940 -- August 6 , 1980  )  was an American writer best known for penning the adapted screenplay for the hit film Grease .
He was born October 8 , 1940 in Alabama .
He also co-wrote the screenplay for the 1980 Village People film Ca n't Stop the Music with Grease producer Allan Carr .
He also wrote a novel , Meet Me at the Melba .
Raised in Atlanta , he died of hepatitis-related liver failure at the age of 39 on August 6 , 1980 in Los Angeles , California .
